Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You may watch the recording above. PARLIAMENT - The Minister of Sport has weighed in on the Ashwin Willemse debacle. Tokozile Xasa called for the suspension of Nick Mallett and Naas Botha following Willemse’s walkout in studio on Saturday. She urged South Africans to unite, build a cohesive society while also exposing racist elements. WATCH: Rugby analyst Ashwin Willemse walks off SuperSport set On Monday SuperSport and MultiChoice said there wasn’t any racism involved in the tiff. Xasa says she is sticking to her statement until an investigation into the matter is concluded. "I met with them and they also demonstrated commitment to deal with the matter. Yes it’s fine. It is only then that I will review my statement but my statement still stands." eNCA